00:36:45,295 --> 00:36:47,597
and the thing I learned was how to stop being a perfectionist

753
00:36:48,338 --> 00:36:49,959
and it's probably something a lot of us suffer from

754
00:36:51,460 --> 00:36:54,723
maybe I might not be as afflicted with this as some people

755
00:36:55,083 --> 00:36:55,863
the other way of saying it is

756
00:36:56,184 --> 00:36:56,884
fuck it, that'll do

757
00:36:56,904 --> 00:36:56,924
I

758
00:36:59,286 --> 00:37:02,388
I do have this problem

759
00:37:03,409 --> 00:37:07,452
and I've kind of learnt a range of ways of trying to snap myself out of perfectionism

760
00:37:07,472 --> 00:37:10,254
trying to just let it go, just trying to move on

761
00:37:11,235 --> 00:37:11,355
and

762
00:37:13,343 --> 00:37:15,864
The main thing is every time I come back to work, I just ask myself,

763
00:37:16,424 --> 00:37:18,786
is this thing I'm working on the most important thing left to do?

764
00:37:18,866 --> 00:37:22,248
If I can only do one more thing before it just gets cast out into the world

765
00:37:22,288 --> 00:37:24,589
without any further input from me, is this what I would be working on?

766
00:37:25,429 --> 00:37:27,350
And 90% of the time the answer is no,

767
00:37:27,610 --> 00:37:29,611
there's something much, much more important I should be working on.

768
00:37:31,352 --> 00:37:35,014
And so I keep like a to-do list that's in priority order as best I can.

769
00:37:35,034 --> 00:37:37,295
I try and, you know, put the most important things next.

770
00:37:38,616 --> 00:37:39,717
And I constantly reconsider it.

771
00:37:40,437 --> 00:37:42,578
And I also have to...

772
00:37:43,551 --> 00:37:47,518
use mental tricks to get over the pain of having to cut features.

773
00:37:47,859 --> 00:37:49,742
Like, when you put things in priority order, then...

774
00:37:51,764 --> 00:37:54,767
What you really need to be doing is when you're adding a big new idea to a game

775
00:37:55,147 --> 00:37:57,449
you should be cutting something out right you only got some amount of time

776
00:37:57,489 --> 00:38:00,872
and probably planned it reasonably well so that it's not going to take forever

777
00:38:01,232 --> 00:38:03,374
and if you can add something major you should be taking something away

778
00:38:03,874 --> 00:38:05,416
but emotionally I can't do that

779
00:38:06,276 --> 00:38:07,758
I'm too attached to everything that's already there

780
00:38:08,158 --> 00:38:10,780
and I don't want to like not write down the great new idea I just had

781
00:38:11,241 --> 00:38:13,062
so instead I just try and put them in priority order

782
00:38:13,542 --> 00:38:14,523
and it's kind of a trick I learned from.

783
00:38:15,925 --> 00:38:18,508
uh, writing about games, I would often be way over the word count

784
00:38:18,889 --> 00:38:21,072
and I couldn't bring myself to just cut out whole paragraphs

785
00:38:21,452 --> 00:38:24,076
so I'd just go through it and I'd just like indent the paragraphs

786
00:38:24,116 --> 00:38:25,698
that weren't quite as good as the other ones

787
00:38:26,259 --> 00:38:28,702
um, and once you do that, and you realise

788
00:38:29,123 --> 00:38:30,344
you look at the word count and realise

789
00:38:30,365 --> 00:38:31,666
oh, all those ones I indented

790
00:38:32,502 --> 00:38:34,304
equal the number of words I've gone over.

791
00:38:34,965 --> 00:38:37,147
So if I cut them all right now, then I'm done.

792
00:38:37,387 --> 00:38:39,469
The whole thing just fits and it's fine.

793
00:38:39,889 --> 00:38:41,411
Suddenly it's much easier to make that call.

794
00:38:41,731 --> 00:38:44,574
Whereas if you're going through and actually committing to deleting it right then and there,

795
00:38:44,594 --> 00:38:45,555
it's a nightmare.

796
00:38:46,095 --> 00:38:46,575
So if you do a...

797
00:38:46,956 --> 00:38:49,458
If you have your to-do list in priority order,

798
00:38:49,498 --> 00:38:51,880
if you try and put all your ideas for the games in order of

799
00:38:52,201 --> 00:38:54,843
which is the most important thing not yet done.

800
00:38:55,484 --> 00:38:59,348
then the great thing about that is that you don't ever have to cut anything you

801
00:38:59,368 --> 00:39:02,111
can just pretend you're gonna do it all it's all on the list I'm gonna get to it

