00:39:27,981 --> 00:39:29,323
Which is what I'm going to show you.

810
00:39:29,343 --> 00:39:30,684
This is the camera bug in Gunpoint.

811
00:39:31,124 --> 00:39:36,890
It might not even register as a bug, but probably anyone who works on, like, game feel and kind of tweaking things

812
00:39:37,270 --> 00:39:38,091
is looking at this and kind of...

813
00:39:40,715 --> 00:39:44,502
When you climb up a wall and get onto the roof,

814
00:39:45,082 --> 00:39:47,106
the artist, John Roberts, has done this brilliant,

815
00:39:47,206 --> 00:39:49,189
beautiful, smooth animation for clambering up.

816
00:39:49,269 --> 00:39:51,633
I love it, it's kind of sprightly and cool.

817
00:39:52,074 --> 00:39:54,758
And I've completely shat all over his work by...

818
00:39:56,280 --> 00:39:59,002
In code, you don't smoothly climb up, you teleport to the roof.

819
00:39:59,262 --> 00:40:02,344
I teleport you there, then I play the animation of the climbing up happening.

820
00:40:02,724 --> 00:40:06,967
And the camera is following your true location, not the animation, so it just snaps to being

821
00:40:07,087 --> 00:40:07,348
above.

822
00:40:07,828 --> 00:40:10,370
And if the view is scrolling, then you get this annoying little jerk.

823
00:40:10,730 --> 00:40:13,372
And the fact that it's looping constantly as I'm saying this is really pissing some

824
00:40:13,392 --> 00:40:13,732
people off.

